&lt;Trans-Canada Resources Ltd>said an Alberta court on March 6 granted it an extension toApril 6 from March 9 on Trans-Canada's filing of a plan ofarrangement with the court and extended to May 22 a stay oflegal proceedings against the company.    The court also ruled that shareholders' and creditors'smeetings must occur by May 4, Trans-Canada said. Reuter&#3;